	(gr_text "IF YOU ARE READING THIS WITH A \nMICROSCOPE, JUST KNOW THAT THIS \nABSOLUTE MONSTROSITY TOOK ME OVER \n30 GRUELING HOURS OF MY LIFE TO \nDESIGN AND ROUTE. THIRTY. HOURS. \nOF PURE, UNADULTERATED CHAOS. \nTRACE BY TRACE, COMPONENT BY \nCOMPONENT, STARING AT THIS SCREEN \nUNTIL MY EYES BLED, FLIPPING BACK \nAND FORTH BETWEEN THE LAYERS, \nDETANGLING A NONSENSICAL WEB OF \nCOPPER, AND MANUALLY ROUTING EVERY \nSINGLE TRACK JUST TO CLEAR DRILL \nCLEARANCES AND DRAG MY WAY THROUGH \nENDLESS DESIGN RULE ERRORS. I AM \nCONVINCED HARDWARE ROUTING IS A \nFORM OF PSYCHOLOGICAL WARFARE. \nEVERY TIME I FIXED ONE TRACE, THREE \nMORE BROKE. IT WAS AN ENDLESS LOOP \nOF MISERY, BUT IT IS FINALLY DONE. \nIT FINALLY WORKS. SUNPI IS ALIVE. \nREVISION 1.0 IS LOCKED IN, AND I \nAM NEVER TOUCHING THIS CANVAS AGAIN. \nBUILT WITH BLOOD, SWEAT, TEARS, \nAND WAY TOO MUCH CAFFEINE. HY OUT."
